Targeting

--> Scan Multiple IPs
nmap 192.168.1.1 192.168.1.5 192.168.1.10
Scans each listed IP.
Use when: Checking specific devices.

--> Scan an IP Range
nmap 192.168.1.1-20
Scans all IPs from .1 to .20.
Use when: Scanning part of a network.

--> Scan Entire Subnet
nmap 192.168.1.0/24
Scans all 254 hosts in the subnet.
Use when: Full network scan.

--> Scan Targets from a File
nmap -iL targets.txt
Reads IP addresses from a text file (one per line).
Use when: You have many targets to scan.

--> Exclude Specific IPs
nmap 192.168.1.0/24 --exclude 192.168.1.1,192.168.1.5
Scans the range but skips the listed IPs.
Use when: You want to avoid scanning critical servers.
